TITLE: Implementing Actions in XState State Machine
DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive example demonstrating different types of actions (entry, exit, transition) and their implementations in an XState machine configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/guides/actions.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const triggerMachine = createMachine(
  {
    id: 'trigger',
    initial: 'inactive',
    states: {
      inactive: {
        on: {
          TRIGGER: {
            target: 'active',
            // transition actions
            actions: ['activate', 'sendTelemetry']
          }
        }
      },
      active: {
        // entry actions
        entry: ['notifyActive', 'sendTelemetry'],
        // exit actions
        exit: ['notifyInactive', 'sendTelemetry'],
        on: {
          STOP: { target: 'inactive' }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  {
    actions: {
      // action implementations
      activate: (context, event) => {
        console.log('activating...');
      },
      notifyActive: (context, event) => {
        console.log('active!');
      },
      notifyInactive: (context, event) => {
        console.log('inactive!');
      },
      sendTelemetry: (context, event) => {
        console.log('time:', Date.now());
      }
    }
  }
);
```

