TITLE: Using useMachine Hook for Local State Management in React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useMachine hook from @xstate/react to manage local state in a React component. The example shows a toggle button component using a state machine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/recipes/react.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { useMachine } from '@xstate/react';
import { toggleMachine } from '../path/to/toggleMachine';

function Toggle() {
  const [current, send] = useMachine(toggleMachine);

  return (
    <button onClick={() => send('TOGGLE')}>
      {current.matches('inactive') ? 'Off' : 'On'}
    </button>
  );
}
```

