TITLE: Parent-Child Communication in XState
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement parent-child communication in XState using the onReceive function in a callback invocation. It demonstrates a ping-pong interaction between the parent and child.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/guides/communication.md#2025-04-20_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const pingPongMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'pinger',
  initial: 'active',
  states: {
    active: {
      invoke: {
        id: 'ponger',
        src: (context, event) => (callback, onReceive) => {
          // Whenever parent sends 'PING',
          // send parent 'PONG' event
          onReceive((e) => {
            if (e.type === 'PING') {
              callback('PONG');
            }
          });
        }
      },
      entry: send({ type: 'PING' }, { to: 'ponger' }),
      on: {
        PONG: { target: 'done' }
      }
    },
    done: {
      type: 'final'
    }
  }
});
const actor = interpret(pingPongMachine);
actor.subscribe({ complete: () => done() });
actor.start();
```

