TITLE: Spawning Callback Actor with Counter Interval
DESCRIPTION: Example of spawning a callback actor that maintains a counter and responds to increment events while updating count periodically.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/guides/actors.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const counterInterval = (callback, receive) => {
  let count = 0;

  const intervalId = setInterval(() => {
    callback({ type: 'COUNT.UPDATE', count });
    count++;
  }, 1000);

  receive(event => {
    if (event.type === 'INC') {
      count++;
    }
  });

  return () => { clearInterval(intervalId); }
}

const machine = createMachine({
  // ...
  {
    actions: assign({
      counterRef: () => spawn(counterInterval)
    })
  }
  // ...
});
```

