TITLE: Creating EventByType Utility Type for XState Store Events
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a custom EventByType utility type that extracts the specific type of store event where Type matches the event's type property. This enables type-safe event handling for specific event types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/packages/xstate-store/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-20_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { type EventFromStore, type Store } from '@xstate/store';

/**
 * Extract the event where `Type` matches the event's `type` from the given
 * `Store`.
 */
type EventByType<
  TStore extends Store<any, any>,
  // creates a type-safe relationship between `Type` and the `type` keys of the
  // store's events
  Type extends EventFromStore<TStore>['type']
> = Extract<EventFromStore<TStore>, { type: Type }>;
```

