TITLE: Nested Parallel State Nodes in XState
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates a more complex state machine with nested parallel states. It shows a traffic light system where the 'red' state contains parallel sub-states for 'walkSign' and 'pedestrian'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/guides/parallel.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const lightMachine = createMachine({
  // not a parallel machine
  id: 'light',
  initial: 'green',
  states: {
    green: {
      on: {
        TIMER: { target: 'yellow' }
      }
    },
    yellow: {
      on: {
        TIMER: { target: 'red' }
      }
    },

    // nested parallel machine
    red: {
      type: 'parallel',
      states: {
        walkSign: {
          initial: 'solid',
          states: {
            solid: {
              on: {
                COUNTDOWN: { target: 'flashing' }
              }
            },
            flashing: {
              on: {
                STOP_COUNTDOWN: { target: 'solid' }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        pedestrian: {
          initial: 'walk',
          states: {
            walk: {
              on: {
                COUNTDOWN: { target: 'wait' }
              }
            },
            wait: {
              on: {
                STOP_COUNTDOWN: { target: 'stop' }
              }
            },
            stop: {
              type: 'final'
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
});

console.log(lightMachine.transition('yellow', { type: 'TIMER' }).value);
// {
//   red: {
//     walkSign: 'solid',
//     pedestrian: 'walk'
//   }
// }
```

