TITLE: Implementing a Beeping Activity in XState
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to implement a 'beeping' activity in XState. It defines a toggle machine with an active state that has a beeping activity, and demonstrates how to start and stop the activity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/fr/guides/activities.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const toggleMachine = createMachine(
  {
    id: 'toggle',
    initial: 'inactive',
    states: {
      inactive: {
        on: {
          TOGGLE: { target: 'active' }
        }
      },
      active: {
        // The 'beeping' activity will take place as long as
        // the machine is in the 'active' state
        activities: ['beeping'],
        on: {
          TOGGLE: { target: 'inactive' }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  {
    activities: {
      beeping: () => {
        // Start the beeping activity
        const interval = setInterval(() => console.log('BEEP!'), 1000);

        // Return a function that stops the beeping activity
        return () => clearInterval(interval);
      }
    }
  }
);
```

