TITLE: Using Raise Action in XState State Machine (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the usage of the raise action creator to queue an event to the statechart in the internal event queue. This action sends the event immediately on the current 'step' of the interpreter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/statelyai/xstate/blob/main/docs/fr/guides/actions.md#2025-04-20_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createMachine, raise } from 'xstate';

const raiseActionDemo = createMachine({
  id: 'raisedmo',
  initial: 'entry',
  states: {
    entry: {
      on: {
        STEP: {
          target: 'middle'
        },
        RAISE: {
          target: 'middle',
          // immediately invoke the NEXT event for 'middle'
          actions: raise({ type: 'NEXT' })
        }
      }
    },
    middle: {
      on: {
        NEXT: { target: 'last' }
      }
    },
    last: {
      on: {
        RESET: { target: 'entry' }
      }
    }
  }
});
```

